1
00:00:03,761 --> 00:00:10,974
Modest natural growth
is the advice of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

2
00:00:11,190 --> 00:00:14,281
[KGB Double Agent | Allegiance]

3
00:00:15,121 --> 00:00:20,132
All of what we’re hearing
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, Vaiṣṇava,

4
00:00:20,132 --> 00:00:25,262
is making some impression 
upon the heart.

5
00:00:27,261 --> 00:00:33,770
We’ve been accepted
by Guru and Vaiṣṇava.

6
00:00:34,366 --> 00:00:43,775
I remember contemplating going to
the temple in San Francisco and joining

7
00:00:43,775 --> 00:00:47,742
—this is a few days before joining,
making that decision—

8
00:00:47,742 --> 00:00:52,079
and I’m reading Bhagavad-gītā
and in one purport

9
00:00:52,079 --> 00:00:59,679
Prabhupād’s quoting
the famous śloka of the Rāmāyaṇa

10
00:00:59,679 --> 00:01:03,018
where Rāmachandra is saying,

11
00:01:03,018 --> 00:01:07,300
“Once I accept someone 
it’s forever.”

12
00:01:07,332 --> 00:01:09,740
And once someone says,

13
00:01:09,740 --> 00:01:15,657
“My dear Lord Kṛṣṇa,
please accept me”, it’s forever.

14
00:01:15,657 --> 00:01:25,836
It comes when Vibhīṣaṇa, Rāvaṇa’s brother,
has switched sides;

15
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:32,197
he’s left Rāvaṇa and
he’s serving Rāmachandra,

16
00:01:32,197 --> 00:01:36,364
but so many unusual things
are happening

17
00:01:36,364 --> 00:01:41,312
that devotees are
becoming suspicious of him

18
00:01:41,312 --> 00:01:47,753
and thinking he’s like
a classic KGB double agent.

19
00:01:47,753 --> 00:01:53,087
I don’t now if Vibhīṣaṇa
was Russian or not.

20
00:01:53,087 --> 00:01:57,298
But he understood this double agent,
or they thought.

21
00:01:57,298 --> 00:01:59,563
So, some were telling Rāmachandra,

22
00:01:59,563 --> 00:02:03,976
"Oust him.
He’s really an agent of the enemy.

23
00:02:03,976 --> 00:02:07,899
Because too many mysterious things
are going against us."

24
00:02:07,899 --> 00:02:10,034
And Rāmachandra said,
“No, you don’t understand.

25
00:02:10,034 --> 00:02:19,361
Once I accept someone as mine,
that’s forever; that cannot be broken.”

26
00:02:19,669 --> 00:02:26,801
So, being accepted by Kṛṣṇa
through His agents,

27
00:02:26,801 --> 00:02:31,922
we may not be aware of the full implication
of all of these things,

28
00:02:31,922 --> 00:02:40,517
but Guru Mahārāj says it’s the opinion of
Mahāprabhu and the higher Vaiṣṇavas

29
00:02:40,517 --> 00:02:44,103
that once you’ve
—on any level, however remotely—

30
00:02:44,103 --> 00:02:50,731
appreciated hearing about Kṛṣṇa
from a substantial agent,

31
00:02:50,731 --> 00:02:55,450
that the flag has been planted
in the heart.

32
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:59,847
Ultimately that real conceptual seed,
it’s there.

33
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:02,315
It may become suppressed
from time to time,

34
00:03:02,315 --> 00:03:10,464
but it will ultimately assert itself 
being nourished

35
00:03:10,464 --> 00:03:13,737
by Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, and Vaiṣṇava,

36
00:03:13,737 --> 00:03:19,552
and fully express itself and then
spread its influence all over the heart

37
00:03:19,552 --> 00:03:23,295
and, as Guru Mahārāj says,
then tell all the fleeting desires,

38
00:03:23,295 --> 00:03:26,428
“Anyābhilāṣitā-śūnyaṁ,
jñāna-karmādy-anāvṛtam” (Brs: 1.1.9);

39
00:03:26,428 --> 00:03:31,997
to “Get out. This heart belongs
to me and me alone.”

